      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Peter G. Peterson's Sept. 18 Op-Ed article, ''Our Graying Budget Priorities,'' is simply another polemic against spending on health, particularly the health of the elderly.</p>
        <p>Rather than pit generations  against one other, let's assess the needs of all generations for health, education and improved quality of life.</p>
        <p>PAULA B. DORESS-WORTERS  Newton, Mass., Sept. 18, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a resident scholar in women's studies at Brandeis University.</p>
      </block>
